Ben's Portfolio
Welcome to Ben's Portfolio, a personal web project showcasing my skills, projects, and experience as a developer. This portfolio is designed to highlight my work, provide insight into my background, and make it easy to get in touch.

This portfolio website serves as a central hub to demonstrate my web development skills. It includes details about my past projects, technical proficiencies, and information about myself. This is a responsive, single-page application that works seamlessly on all devices, from mobile phones to desktops.

Features
About Section: Provides an introduction to me and my background.
Projects Section: Displays a gallery of my completed projects with links to GitHub repositories and live demos.
Skills Section: Lists the programming languages, tools, and frameworks I'm proficient in.
Contact Section: Contains a form that visitors can use to reach me directly.
Responsive Design: The website is fully responsive and adapts to different screen sizes for optimal viewing on any device.
Technologies Used
HTML5: For structuring the content of the website.
CSS3: For styling and layout, with responsiveness ensured by CSS media queries.
JavaScript: Adds interactivity to the website.
Git & GitHub: For version control and project hosting.